<subSubSection lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,1274,2020]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,1314,1340]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Remarks.</emphasis>
Ballantyne believes 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[566,735,1314,1340]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="417 - 422" refId="ref107053" refString="Olivier, E. (1913) Lampyridae. Resultats de L'Expedition Scientifique Neerlandaise a la Nouvelle-Guinee en 1907 et 1909 sous les auspices de Dr H. R. Lorentz. Zoologie Livraison III. Nova Guinea 9, 417 - 422." type="journal article" year="1913">Olivier (1913)</bibRefCitation>
incorrectly synonymised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1853" box="[1039,1160,1315,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[1039,1160,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">L. limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1883" box="[1218,1376,1315,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis box="[1218,1376,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">L. rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval. Olivier" authorityYear="1913" box="[151,352,1355,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginipennis">
<emphasis box="[151,352,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">L. marginipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both 
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard, C. E." box="[435,659,1354,1380]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="74" refId="ref103341" refString="Blanchard, C. E. (1853) Description des insectes. In: Dumont-D'Urville, J. S. C. Voyage au Pole sud et dans l'Oceanie sur les corvettes l'Astrolabe et la Zelee. Paris, 1842 - 54. Zoologie, t. 4, 73, 74, plates V, VI." type="journal article" year="1853">Blanchard's (1853)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1853" box="[669,857,1355,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[669,857,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Luciola limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier (1883)" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1883" box="[918,1325,1354,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis box="[918,1144,1355,1380]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Luciola rubiginosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E." box="[1154,1325,1354,1380]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="326 - 332" refId="ref106681" refString="Olivier, E. (1883) Lampyrides nouveaux ou peu connus. Revue D'Entomologie 3, 73 - 80, 326 - 332." type="journal article" year="1883">Olivier (1883)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from the Solomons were described with the MS black, consistent with the specimens described here as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blanchard" authorityYear="1853" box="[1297,1428,1395,1420]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[1297,1428,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">M. limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[223,536,1434,1460]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref104737" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1838) Insectes. pp 57 - 302 In: Lesson, M. (Ed.) Voyage autour du monde, execute par ordre du roi, sur la corvette de sa majeste, La Coquille, pendant les annees 1822, 1823, 1824, et 1825 etc. Zoologie. 2, Pt. 2, Div. 1, Ch. xiii. Bertrand: Paris." type="journal volume" year="1838">Guérin-Méneville's (1838)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval. Olivier" authorityYear="1913" box="[542,741,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginipennis">
<emphasis box="[542,741,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">L. marginipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described with a red MS.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,1274,2020]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
This species is not reliably identified in collections due in part to confusion over the actual publication date of 
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[250,570,1514,1540]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref104737" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1838) Insectes. pp 57 - 302 In: Lesson, M. (Ed.) Voyage autour du monde, execute par ordre du roi, sur la corvette de sa majeste, La Coquille, pendant les annees 1822, 1823, 1824, et 1825 etc. Zoologie. 2, Pt. 2, Div. 1, Ch. xiii. Bertrand: Paris." type="journal volume" year="1838">Guérin-Méneville's (1838)</bibRefCitation>
, and also the lack of 
<typeStatus box="[849,899,1514,1540]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
material. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cowan, C. F." box="[1028,1202,1514,1540]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="358 - 360" refId="ref103999" refString="Cowan, C. F. (1970) The Insects of the Coquille Voyage. Journal of the Society for the Bibliography of Natural History 5 (5), 358 - 360." type="journal article" year="1970">Cowan (1970)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bocak, L." box="[1270,1436,1514,1540]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="245 - 251" refId="ref103434" refString="Bocak, L. (1998) Nomenclatural notes on taxa of the family Lycidae described by Guerin-Meneville (Insecta: Coleoptera). Annales Zoologici 48 (3 / 4), 245 - 251." type="journal article" year="1998">Bocák (1998)</bibRefCitation>
resolved the issue of the publication date and their opinions are followed here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1437,1274,2020]" lastBlockId="106.[151,1436,152,298]" lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[199,495,1594,1620]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref104737" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1838) Insectes. pp 57 - 302 In: Lesson, M. (Ed.) Voyage autour du monde, execute par ordre du roi, sur la corvette de sa majeste, La Coquille, pendant les annees 1822, 1823, 1824, et 1825 etc. Zoologie. 2, Pt. 2, Div. 1, Ch. xiii. Bertrand: Paris." type="journal volume" year="1838">Guérin-Méneville (1838)</bibRefCitation>
has been considered the author of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval. Olivier" authorityYear="1913" box="[905,1073,1595,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginipennis">
<emphasis box="[905,1073,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">marginipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in all references to the species since 
<bibRefCitation author="Motschulsky, V. de" box="[219,459,1634,1660]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="47 - 62" refId="ref106522" refString="Motschulsky, V. de (1854) Lampyrides. Etudes Entomologiques III, 47 - 62." type="journal article" year="1854">Motschulsky (1854)</bibRefCitation>
. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Boisduval, J. B. A. D." box="[589,794,1634,1660]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref103521" refString="Boisduval, J. B. A. D. (1835) Voyage de decouvertes de l' Astrolabe, execute par ordre du Roi, pendant les annees 1826 - 1829, sous le commandement de M. J. Dumont-D'Urville. Faune entomologique de l'ocean Pacifique. Deuxieme partie. Coleopteres et autres ordres. Paris. 716 pp." type="book" year="1835">Boisduval (1835)</bibRefCitation>
attributed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1835" box="[921,1207,1635,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginipennis">
<emphasis box="[921,1207,1635,1660]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Lampyris marginipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to Guérin-Méneville, Boisduval's description of the species is the first published use of the name to be associated with a description, although it is impossible to determine the sex. His specimens were taken in 'Ile Waigiou’, which is probably Waigeo (130E, 0S) off the NW tip of Irian Jaya. 
<bibRefCitation author="Guerin-Meneville, F. E." box="[854,1169,1754,1780]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref104737" refString="Guerin-Meneville, F. E. (1838) Insectes. pp 57 - 302 In: Lesson, M. (Ed.) Voyage autour du monde, execute par ordre du roi, sur la corvette de sa majeste, La Coquille, pendant les annees 1822, 1823, 1824, et 1825 etc. Zoologie. 2, Pt. 2, Div. 1, Ch. xiii. Bertrand: Paris." type="journal volume" year="1838">Guérin-Méneville's (1838)</bibRefCitation>
work has consistently been quoted in the literature as 1830 and both 
<bibRefCitation author="Laporte, F. L. de" box="[730,911,1794,1820]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="122 - 153" refId="ref105326" refString="Laporte, F. L. de (1833) Essai d'une revision du genre Lampyre. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 122 - 153." type="book chapter" year="1833">Laporte (1833)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Boisduval, J. B. A. D." box="[975,1184,1794,1820]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" refId="ref103521" refString="Boisduval, J. B. A. D. (1835) Voyage de decouvertes de l' Astrolabe, execute par ordre du Roi, pendant les annees 1826 - 1829, sous le commandement de M. J. Dumont-D'Urville. Faune entomologique de l'ocean Pacifique. Deuxieme partie. Coleopteres et autres ordres. Paris. 716 pp." type="book" year="1835">Boisduval (1835)</bibRefCitation>
had apparently seen Guérin-Méneville's work long before it was published (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[809,1016,1834,1860]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="161 - 165" refId="ref102834" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1988) The identities of Luciola australis (F.) and L. guerini Laporte (Coleoptera: Lampyridae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society 27, 161 - 165." type="journal article" year="1988">Ballantyne, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Guérin-Méneville's description of the antepenultimate abdominal segment yellow and the penultimate emarginated indicates he based 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boisduval" authorityYear="1835" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lampyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Lampyris marginipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on a female. However the specimen was 
<quantity box="[817,885,1914,1940]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long and taken in Papua at ‘Offak’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Lea, A. M." box="[1323,1435,1914,1940]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="45 - 251" refId="ref105431" refString="Lea, A. M. (1909) Revision of the Australian and Tasmanian Malacodermidae. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1909, 45 - 251. [Lampyridae, 106 - 111]." type="journal article" year="1909">Lea 1909</bibRefCitation>
thought this could have been Mt Arfak). While this study has not revealed any species with orange pronotum, dark brown elytra with lateral pale margins from the island of New 
<collectingCountry box="[934,1022,1994,2020]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, several 
<taxonomicName box="[1123,1212,1995,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1123,1212,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Luciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="106" lastPageNumber="107" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1267,1380,1995,2020]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Pteroptyx</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with colouration of orange pronotum and dark elytra are known (these also conform to the smaller size described) (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[290,503,192,218]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref102757" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne 1987a</bibRefCitation>
; work in progress). 
<bibRefCitation author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[742,928,192,218]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" refId="ref104034" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1837) Catalogue des Coleopteres de la collection de M. Le Comte Dejean 4 th edition, 1 - 176. Mequignon-Marvis, Paris." type="book" year="1837">Dejean's (1837)</bibRefCitation>
record is a catalogue name only, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Germar, E. F." pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="153 - 247" refId="ref104533" refString="Germar, E. F. (1848) Beitrage zur Insektenfauna von Adelaide. Linnaea Entomologica III, 153 - 247." type="journal article" year="1848">Germar's (1848)</bibRefCitation>
record of the species from Adelaide is erroneous. [No species of firefly have been recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,258,272,298]" name="Australia" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Australia</collectingCountry>
south of Sydney (
<bibRefCitation author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C." box="[471,816,272,298]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" pagination="15 - 93" refId="ref103088" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2000) Lampyridae of Australia (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae: Luciolini). Memoirs of the Queensland Museum 46 (1), 15 - 93." type="journal article" year="2000">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin 2000</bibRefCitation>
)].
</paragraph>
